  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Aim of our study is to compare immediate full weight-bearing and partial weight-bearing for 6&#xD;
      weeks after a tibial shaft fracture treated with intramedullary nailing. Co-primary outcome&#xD;
      is return to work and physical component scale in the SF-36 questionnaire.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
